State MSM Profile: Idaho

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Idaho

An estimated 9,907 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Idaho in 2013, representing 0.2% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 574,213 adult men of Idaho, 1.7% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Idaho resided in counties within medium or small metropolitan areas (66.9%). No MSM in Idaho resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Idaho, 2013

MSM in Idaho Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Idaho, Ada County had the largest population of MSM at 2,522, representing 25.5% of all MSM in the state. Cassia County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Idaho at 5.5%. This was greater than the percentage for Idaho as a whole, which was 1.7% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Idaho Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Boise City Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Boise City MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Idaho at 3,937, or 39.7% of all MSM in the state. Of the 225,711 adult men in Boise City, an estimated 1.7% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Coeur dAlene Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Coeur dAlene MSA had a population of 896 MSM, or 9.0% of all MSM in Idaho. Of the 51,811 adult men in Coeur dAlene, an estimated 1.7% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Idaho Falls Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Idaho Falls MSA had a population of 820 MSM, or 8.3% of all MSM in Idaho. Of the 45,160 adult men in Idaho Falls, an estimated 1.8% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Pocatello Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Pocatello MSA had a population of 636 MSM, or 6.4% of all MSM in Idaho. Of the 29,714 adult men in Pocatello, an estimated 2.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Lewiston Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Lewiston MSA overlaps two states: Idaho and Washington. The Idaho portion of the MSA had 293 MSM, or 3.0% of all MSM in the state and 76.7% of the 382 MSM in the MSA. Of 15,126 adult men in the Idaho part of Lewiston, 1.9% were MSM. This was greater than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 1.6% of adult men (382 out of 23,319).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Logan Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Logan MSA overlaps two states: Idaho and Utah. The Idaho portion of the MSA had 45 MSM, or 0.5% of all MSM in the state and 6.9% of the 650 MSM in the MSA. Of 4,190 adult men in the Idaho part of Logan, 1.1% were MSM. This was less than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 1.5% of adult men (650 out of 42,799).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
